In TCPView, what does the * mean in the Remote Address field. In TCPView what does the * mean in the remote address field. 1 Answer 1. Those are for listening sockets, i.e. sockets open on your machine waiting to receive incoming connections. If you see a * there, it means the socket is ready for connections from anywhere. If you see a hostname or IP address, then only connections from those are accepted.
